To install Python 3.9 in WSL2, you can follow these steps:

    Open the Windows Terminal or a WSL terminal of your choice (e.g. Ubuntu).

    Update the package index using the following command:

sql

sudo apt-get update

    Install the required dependencies to build Python 3.9 by running:

csharp

sudo apt-get install -y build-essential checkinstall
sudo apt-get install -y libreadline-gplv2-dev libncursesw5-dev libssl-dev \
    libsqlite3-dev tk-dev libgdbm-dev libc6-dev libbz2-dev

    Download the Python 3.9 source code from the official website:

ruby

wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.9.4/Python-3.9.4.tar.xz

    Extract the tar archive:

tar xvf Python-3.9.4.tar.xz

    Enter the extracted directory and configure the build:

bash

cd Python-3.9.4
./configure

    Compile and install Python 3.9:

go

make
sudo make install

    Verify the installation by running the following command:

css

python3.9 --version

This should return the version of Python 3.9 that you just installed.